he filaments. According to the complementary IR data, most filaments have\nassociated Class~II young stellar objects. Class~I objects are mainly found to\nbe located in the filaments with a virial parameter close to 1. Within two\nvirialized filaments, $^{12}$CO outflows have been detected, indicating ongoing\nstar-forming activity therein.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 Jul 2019 13:12:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 21 Aug 2019 08:01:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-22"}
