licities. The light metals show typical PG\n1159-type abundances and the elemental composition is in good agreement with\npredictions from AFTP evolutionary models. However, the expansion ages do not\nagree with evolution timescales expected from the AFTP scenario and\nalternatives should be explored.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 Jul 2019 15:05:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-31"}
