ophily with processes imposing constraints on degree\ndistributions. We show that the effects of homophily on clustering are robust\nwith respect to distribution constraints, while degree assortativity can be\nhighly dependent on the particular kind of enforced degree sequence.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 Jul 2019 15:12:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 17 Jul 2019 00:34:45 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 2 Apr 2020 13:08:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-03"}
